    "updated_at": "2011-06-25T18:23:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My take on this is to be conservative for now.  `-pylab` is special because it's extremely widely documented, so we don't really want everyone's scripts, aliases and habits to break everywhere.  We'll have to fine-tune our handling of command-line args after more extensive field use and feedback, so I'd suggest we stick, for now, to the bare minimum of tweaks until we can collect such information post-0.11.\n"
  },
